==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Statement
<hw>State"ment</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧t"m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of stating, reciting, or presenting, orally or
on paper; <as>as, to interrupt a speaker in the <ex>statement</ex> of
his case</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is stated; a formal embodiment in
language of facts or opinions; a narrative; a recital.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Admirable perspicuity of <xex>statement</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Brougham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Statemonger</ent>⟦br⟧
